<p>To assess the progress of HPE Helion Cloud update, the progress utility provides an overview of the update status.</p>
<p>This provides an option to get a snapshot of the current state or to monitor the update progress.</p>
<section id="view-the-current-status"> <title>View the current status</title>
<p>To get a snapshot of current status of HPE Helion OpenStack update:</p>
<ol>
<li>
<p>Log in the seed VM host.</p>

<codeblock>
<codeph>sudo su -
</codeph>
</codeblock>
</li>
<li>
<p>SSH to the seed VM.</p>

<codeblock>
<codeph>ssh root@192.0.2.1 
</codeph>
</codeblock>
</li>
<li>
<p>Run the following commands:</p>

<codeblock>
<codeph>cd /opt/stack/tripleo-ansible/update_helpers/
./progress.sh
</codeph>
</codeblock>
</li>
</ol>
</section>
<section id="monitor-the-progress"> <title>Monitor the progress</title>
<p>To get a snapshot of current status of HPE Helion update:</p>
<ol>
<li>
<p>Log in the seed VM host.</p>

<codeblock>
<codeph>sudo su -
</codeph>
</codeblock>
</li>
<li>
<p>SSH to the seed VM.</p>

<codeblock>
<codeph>ssh root@192.0.2.1 
</codeph>
</codeblock>
</li>
<li>
<p>Run the following commands:</p>

<codeblock>
<codeph>cd /opt/stack/tripleo-ansible/update_helpers/
./progress.sh --refresh
</codeph>
</codeblock>
</li>
</ol>
